					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540144#post-4363808</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540144/scp-4968#post-4363808</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 14 Sep 2019 20:35:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Pedantique</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3118444</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I was enjoying this article's slow buildup and the increasing absurdity of what is basically a deer terrorist organization, but the ending falls really flat for me. Speculation about a possible leader doesn't feel satisfying as an ending, especially with such a rich setting. I'm at -1, but I would love to be able to flip that around in the future if the ending was developed further.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540144#post-4363802</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540144/scp-4968#post-4363802</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 14 Sep 2019 20:26:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>PrLosash</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5257365</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I enjoy the concept of a meme that is affecting animals rather than humans and I haven't seen such an article in a while. I feel like there were couple (or maybe one) grammar mistakes in the article, but they were minor enough and I forgot what they were.</p> <p>An interesting idea and a solid execution - that why I upvoted.</p> <p>I must note, that I may have glanced over a paragraph or two (instead of reading them), but that was not enough to lower my enjoyment of the article.</p> 
				 	]]>
